tonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 22, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104enc1665702653522.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/enc1665702653522.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/enc1665702653522.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"enc1665702653522\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      /ceo\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Compile entity collection operations and occurrence operations.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"enc1665702653522__section_w2120ab1b5b1_w2121ab1b5_w2122ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"enc1665702653522__p_d148052e1_d148053e1_d148054e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/ceo</span> {<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/inf</span> | <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/war</span>} {<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/lis</span> {<code class=\"ph codeph\">=2</code>}} {<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/tpl</span>} {<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/plt</span>} {<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/aft=</span>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">DateTime</var>} {<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/bef=</span>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">DateTime</var>} {<var class=\"keyword varname\">Entity</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">.</code>}{<var class=\"keyword varname\">Model</var>}}</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"enc1665702653522__section_w2123ab1b5b3_w2124ab1b5_w2125ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1153145e101\">\n                  \n Switches\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"enc1665702653522__li_d51431e1_d51432e1_d51433e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"czj1665702653450.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/czj1665702653450.html\" title=\"Display the information listing plus warning and error messages when compiling.\">/inf</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"enc1665702653522__li_d51434e1_d51435e1_d51436e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wmw1665702653597.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wmw1665702653597.html\" title=\"Display warning and error messages when compiling.\">/war</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"enc1665702653522__li_d51437e1_d51438e1_d51439e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"stn1665702655266.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/stn1665702655266.html\" title=\"Produce compile listings of ProcScript modules for components, application shells, menus, and global ProcScript.\">/lis</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"enc1665702653522__li_d51440e1_d51441e1_d51442e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fmo1665702653737.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fmo1665702653737.html\" title=\"Compiles main development objects that are defined as templates (Purpose = T), but does not generate runtime objects. Use it to ensure that templates do not contain ProcScript syntax errors.\">/tpl</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"enc1665702653522__li_d51443e1_d51444e1_d51445e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"twc1665702654010.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/twc1665702654010.html\" title=\"Compiles main development objects that are defined as palettes (Purpose = P), but does not generate runtime objects. Use it to ensure that palettes do not contain ProcScript syntax errors.\">/plt</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"enc1665702653522__li_d51446e1_d51447e1_d51448e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ide1665702625805.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ide1665702625805.html\" title=\"Compile objects modified after and/or before the date specified.\">/aft= or /bef=</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"enc1665702653522__section_w2126ab1b5b5_w2127ab1b5_w2128ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1153145e183\">\n                  \n Parameters\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"enc1665702653522__d6306e22\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Entity</var>—name of an entity in the specified model. If specified, <var class=\"keyword varname\">Model</var> must also be specified.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"enc1665702653522__d6306e31\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Model</var>—model name or search profile to use as selector for the modeled entities to analyze; if omitted, all application models are analyzed.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"enc1665702653522__section_w2129ab1b5b7_w2130ab1b5_w2131ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1153145e207\">\n                  \n Use With\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"enc1665702653522__d5931e20\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">ide.exe</span>—Uniface IDE</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"enc1665702653522__section_w2132ab1b5b9_w2133ab1b5_w2134ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1153145e219\">\n                  \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"enc1665702653522__p_d148070e1_d148071e1_d148072e1\">By default, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/ceo</span> displays only error messages. (Compiling interactively displays both error and warning messages by default.) Use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/inf</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/war</span>, and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/lis</span> sub-switches to increase the amount of information displayed.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"enc1665702653522__p_d148073e1_d148074e1_d148075e1\">Use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/tpl</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/plt</span> sub-switches if you want to compile modeled entities that are defined as templates or palettes. By default, these are not compiled by the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/ceo</span> switch.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"enc1665702653522__section_w2135ab1b5c11_w2136ab1b5_w2137ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1153145e253\">Example: Using /ceo </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"enc1665702653522__p_d148079e1_d148080e1_d148081e1\">The following example compiles all entity operations changed since 15 September 2016:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">/ceo /aft=15-09-2016</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"enc1665702653522__p_d148082e1_d148083e1_d148084e1\">The following example compiles all entities\n            beginning with ORD in models starting with S.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">/ceo ord*.s*</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xfc1665702625593.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Compiling from the IDE Command Line</a><p>The IDE command line can be used to compile multiple objects without opening the IDE. It is especially useful for automating compilation by means of batch scripts.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527215\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527215\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "/ceo Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 22, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 /ceo Compile entity collection operations and occurrence operations. /ceo { /inf | /war } { /lis { =2 }} { /tpl } { /plt } { /aft= DateTime } { /bef= DateTime } { Entity . }{ Model }} Switches /inf /war /lis /tpl /plt /aft= or /bef= Parameters Entity —name of an entity in the specified model. If specified, Model must also be specified. Model —model name or search profile to use as selector for the modeled entities to analyze; if omitted, all application models are analyzed. Use With ide.exe —Uniface IDE Description By default, /ceo displays only error messages. (Compiling interactively displays both error and warning messages by default.) Use the /inf , /war , and /lis sub-switches to increase the amount of information displayed. Use the /tpl and /plt sub-switches if you want to compile modeled entities that are defined as templates or palettes. By default, these are not compiled by the /ceo switch. Example: Using /ceo The following example compiles all entity operations changed since 15 September 2016: /ceo /aft=15-09-2016 Copy The following example compiles all entities beginning with ORD in models starting with S. /ceo ord*.s* Copy Related Links Compiling from the IDE Command Line The IDE command line can be used to compile multiple objects without opening the IDE. It is especially useful for automating compilation by means of batch scripts. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}